    q: "What does 'specialty grade' mean for wholesale coffee?",
    a: "Specialty grade coffee scores 80 points or above on the Specialty Coffee Association's 100-point scale, evaluated by certified Q Graders. It's produced from arabica varieties, is free of category-one defects, and maintains traceability to its origin. For wholesale buyers, specialty grade means you're starting with a product that can produce excellent cups — but roasting decisions and extraction still determine what ends up in the cup."
  },
