    a: "Specialty wholesale coffee is priced substantially above commodity coffee — typically $10–$18 per pound wholesale versus $3–$6 for commercial grade. The premium reflects higher green coffee costs (direct trade or relationship purchasing above commodity market rates), smaller production batches, more intensive sourcing and quality control, and the knowledge and support that comes with a specialty roaster relationship."
  },
