    q: "Can a small café afford specialty wholesale coffee?",
    a: "Yes, and the economics often work better than expected. The markup on specialty coffee in a café context is substantial — a pound of specialty wholesale coffee at $14 yields 30–35 espresso shots at $4–5 each. The beverage revenue from one pound is $120–$175. The specialty premium over commercial coffee is typically $4–6 per pound — a cost difference that's recovered in the first few shots and more than covered by the guest experience that commands premium pricing."
  },
